                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" fkcefr="c2" hclass="sense" id="academyaward_sng_1" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">one of the awards given every year by the US Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences for achievement in the making of films</span></span><div class="collapse" hclass="collapse" htag="div"><span class="unbox" unbox="cult" source="ald9_guide" id="academyaward_unbox_1"><span class="box_title">Culture</span><span class="body"><span class="p"><span class="dh">Academy Awards</span> are presented every February or March in <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/los-angeles" title="Los Angeles definition"><span class="ndv">Los Angeles</span></a> by <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-academy-of-motion-picture-arts-and-sciences" title="the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences definition"><span class="ndv">the Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences</span></a>. The awards were first presented in 1929 by <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/douglas-fairbanks" title="Douglas Fairbanks definition"><span class="ndv">Douglas Fairbanks</span></a>. Winners receive a small metal statue, and the most important ones are for ‘Best Actor’, ‘Best Actress’, ‘Best Picture’ and ‘Best Director’.</span></span></span></div><span class="topic-g"><span class="prefix">Topics </span><a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/topic/success?level=c2" title="Topic success"><span class="topic" href="l2:notions:success?cefr=c2"><span class="topic_name">Success</span><span class="topic_cefr">c2</span></span></a></span><div class="collapse" hclass="collapse" htag="div"><span class="unbox" unbox="snippet" id="academyaward_unbox_2"><span class="box_title">Oxford Collocations Dictionary</s